ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: A course that gives you a good historical review about how we measure and study the physical and chemical properties of the earth's interior.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I have a better appreciation for the difficulty associated in estimating the properties of the earth's interior. I also better appreciate the interdisciplinary nature of the field. The need for good theory in the field to make predictive progress in the field was also instilled
